        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:09PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 609 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Emerson, or 11 miles northeast of Whiteville, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rowan, Lake Waccamaw, Sandyfield, Carvers, Lisbon, Lagoon, Elkton,
Council, Emerson, Kelly, Clarkton, White Lake, Bolton, and East
Arcadia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
